# WaterRisingProject

A multi-agent writing assistant that parses Obsidian notes, builds a hybrid semantic + tag retrieval layer, and coordinates LLM agents. The project uses FAISS for vector search and n8n for workflow automation.

## Quick start

1. Clone repository and create a Python 3.12 virtual environment:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourname/WaterRisingProject.git
   cd WaterRisingProject
   python3 -m venv .venv
   source .venv/bin/activate
   ```
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install --upgrade pip
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   # optional dev tools
   pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
   ```
3. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set `OPENAI_API_KEY`.

## Common commands

Task | Command
-----|-------
Run tests | `pytest -q`
Coverage | `pytest --cov=src`
Format/lint | `ruff check . && black --check .`
Build index | `python tests/build_index.py`
Chat with Nary | `python src/main.py`

Scripts under `tests/` also demonstrate parsing Obsidian markdown and chunking text for embeddings.

## n8n automation

n8n can automate routine tasks such as running tests, rebuilding the FAISS index, and sending notifications. See [docs/n8n_integration_plan.md](docs/n8n_integration_plan.md) for a detailed workflow.

## Project status

- Parsing of chapter and character metadata implemented in example scripts.
- Hybrid tag + semantic retrieval utilities implemented and tested.
- Work continues on agent interactions and narrative feedback loops.

For more details, see [docs/README.md](docs/README.md).
